observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Engineer coordinate, monitor and evaluate the implementation of the PPAs to maximize the utilization of 20% DF; and
We also reiterate the following previous recommendations: 

that the Municipal government officials and the Municipal  Development Council through the Municipal Planning and  Development Officer (MPDO) properly plan, prioritize all activities and evaluate the socio-economic development and environmental management programs and projects to be implemented during the year;

that the Council reassess the necessity of pursuing the unimplemented projects, otherwise reprogram the same together with the allotments for projects that are not among the items allowed under DBM and DILG JMC No. 2011-1 to a more needed developmental projects;

that the MPDO submit justification within five days for the utilization of funds amounting to ₱2,093,111.00 for the items disallowed by the Sangguniang Panlalawigan and by JMC No. 2011-1 dated April 13, 2011; and

that the Municipal Development Council and Budget Officer appropriate sufficient fund for the complete implementation of the identified projects.

We recommended that the:
Individual Accountable Officers granted with cash advances (a) strictly observe diligence in the liquidation of their respective cash advances within the prescribed period, (b) return the excess cash advances, if any, simultaneously with the liquidation report, and (c) in case of cancelled travel, immediately and fully refund the cash advance and submit valid justification for not pursuing the proposed travel;

Accountable Officers with cash advances ensure that the required supporting documents for the project activity of different offices are immediately submitted to the Municipal Accountant;

The Municipal Accountant and Treasurer closely monitor the liquidation of cash advances and issue demand letters to concerned officials and employees with cash advances that remained unsettled for more than thirty (30) days; and
The Municipal Treasurer withhold the salaries due to officials and employees concerned with overdue unliquidated cash advances and those with previously issued demand letter to prevent misappropriation of public funds, overstatement of Due from Officers and Employees account and understatement of affected expense accounts for a given period.

We recommended that:

Ms. Melogean S. Candelario provide for the complete necessary documents relative to her requests for relief from accountability inclusive of a strong and valid justification for her delayed application in compliance with the provisions of COA Memorandum No. 92-751 and Sec. 499 of GAAM Vol. I, in order to ensure or facilitate the evaluation and resolution of applications;

In case of non-compliance by the MSWDO, the Municipal Mayor, Accountant and Treasurer enforce immediate and full refund of the book value of the property subject of the request for relief, to be determined by the Municipal Accountant;

In case of non-settlement the Municipal Mayor, Property Officer, Accountant, and Treasurer ensure that no clearance would be granted to the MSWDO until full settlement of her accountability; and

The Municipal Accountant and Property Officer make pertinent adjustments on their records to reflect the loss of the IT equipment. Moreover, the Municipal Accountant discloses the matter on the Notes to Financial Statements.

